Suba
----

Author: Jesse Dailey <jesse.dailey@gmail.com>

Suba is a fast template engine.  Inspired by python's Mod (%) operator's string substitution.

Example:

>>> template(text="This is a test of %(who)s.", who="Suba")
'This is a test of Suba.'


Unlike the Mod operator, you can include ANY valid python as the substitution expression, not just key names.

Example:

>>> template(text="These are numbers: %( " ".join((x+x for x in range(1,10))) )")
'These are numbers: 2 4 6 8 10 12 14 16 18'

>>> template(text="""
... %(def macro(x):)
...		%(x)d. line-item.
... %/
... These are some lines:
... %(for i in range(3):)
...		%(macro(i))
... %/
... """)
'
These are lines:
1. line-item
2. line-item
3. line-item
'



